      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/multi-study-hemolysis-synthesis",
      "type": "uofa:Evidence",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modelling studies (Giersiepen, Zhang, Taskin, Bludszuweit)",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis drawing on four independent published hemolysis modelling studies spanning 1990–2015. The synthesis reconciles differing power-law exponents for the modified Giersiepen-Wurzinger model, establishes consensus parameter ranges for shear-stress thresholds, and provides a pooled empirical baseline for absolute hemolysis index prediction in centrifugal pumps. Because this node consolidates findings from multiple peer-reviewed sources, the evidentiary weight is considered self-evident from the published record and no single upstream derivation edge is encoded."
    },
